'''自發演替'''（{{Lang-en|autogenic succession}}）是指由生態系統內的[[生物因子|生物因素]]驅動的[[演替|演替]]，虽然自發演替的机制长期以来一直存在争议，但人們很早就意識到了生物演替過程中起到的作用。<ref>Cowles, Henry Chandler (1899). "The Ecological Relations of the Vegetation on the Sand Dunes of Lake Michigan. Part I.-Geographical Relations of the Dune Floras". ''Botanical Gazette''. '''27''' (2): 95–117. [[International_Standard_Serial_Number|ISSN]] 0006-8071.</ref><ref>Cowles, Henry C. (1911). "The Causes of Vegetational Cycles". ''Annals of the Association of American Geographers''. '''1''': 3–20. [[Digital_object_identifier|doi]]:10.2307/2560843. [[International_Standard_Serial_Number|ISSN]] 0004-5608.</ref><ref>Finegan, Bryan (1984). "Forest succession". ''Nature''. '''312''' (5990): 109–114. [[Digital_object_identifier|doi]]:10.1038/312109a0. [[International_Standard_Serial_Number|ISSN]] 1476-4687</ref>目前，學界主流的共识是促进、耐受和抑制机制都對自發演替有作用。<ref>Connell, Joseph H.; Slatyer, Ralph O. (1977). "Mechanisms of Succession in Natural Communities and Their Role in Community Stability and Organization". ''The American Naturalist''. '''111''' (982): 1119–1144. [[International_Standard_Serial_Number|ISSN]] 0003-0147.</ref>演替的概念通常与植被和森林群落相关，但它也适用于更广泛的生态系统。與此相反的概念是[[異發演替|異發演替]]，它是指由生态系统的[[非生物因子|非生物因子]]驱动的演替。<ref name="ORO" />

== 作用機制 ==
植物本身（生物組分）可以导致演替发生。

* 葉片捕捉日光
* 碎屑的产生
* 水分和养分吸收
* [[固氮|固氮]]
* 人为气候变化

这些方面使特定地点的生態逐渐發生改變。由于存在既有的植物生命體，自發演替可視作一種[[次生演替|次生演替]]。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Archived copy|url=https://www.epa.gov/ecopage/upland/oak/oak94/Proceedings/Platt1.gif|publisher=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081020120925/https://www.epa.gov/ecopage/upland/oak/oak94/Proceedings/Platt1.gif|archive-date=20 October 2008}}</ref>

=== 促進 ===

* 改善场地因素，如增加有机质

=== 抑制 ===

* 阻碍物种或生长

